My daughter Olivia would have been 6 years old today. To honor her, I'm kicking off fundraising for my 7th Extra Life, a 24-hour gaming marathon, to support Lurie Children's Hospital in Chicago. 

Today only, I'll be matching any & all donations up to $1000.

Since 2014, Bert Fanslow, Alan Spadoni and I have raised just short of $19,000 for Lurie, thanks to the incredible generosity of people like you. We know times are tough, but we'd greatly appreciate your contribution to our cause, no matter how big. Even spreading the word about our mission is a great help.

And if you'd like to raise money for your local children's hospital while playing video games for 24 hours, we'd love to have you join Team Olivia. Just visit our team page and click on the green Join Team button.

Thank you so much for your support and encouragement over the years. It truly means a lot to us.
